def get_new_command(command):
    # If --set-upstream or -u are passed, remove it and its argument. This is
    # because the remaining arguments are concatenated onto the command suggested
    # by git, which includes --set-upstream and its argument
    upstream_option = '--set-upstream'
    if upstream_option in command.script_parts:
        upstream_option_index = command.script_parts.index(upstream_option)
        command.script_parts.pop(upstream_option_index)  # Remove --set-upstream
        command.script_parts.pop(upstream_option_index)  # Remove its argument
    else:
        upstream_option = '-u'
        if upstream_option in command.script_parts:
            upstream_option_index = command.script_parts.index(upstream_option)
            command.script_parts.pop(upstream_option_index)  # Remove -u
            command.script_parts.pop(upstream_option_index)  # Remove its argument

    last_line = command.stderr.strip().split('\n')[-1]
    push_upstream = f"origin {last_line.split()[-1]}"

    return replace_argument(" ".join(command.script_parts), 'push', push_upstream)
